    <summary>Sights and Sounds of Digital Modes</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
Fldigi is a modem program for most of the digital modes used by radio amateurs today: CW, PSK, MFSK, RTTY, Hell, DominoEX, Olivia, and Throb are all supported. It can help calibrate a sound card to a time signal and do frequency measurement tests.

![screenshot](https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/chtof/chocolatey-packages/automatic/fldigi/screenshot.png)

### Package Specific
#### Package Parameters
The following package parameter can be set:

* `/DIR:` Where to install the program, defaults to "`C:\Program Files(x86)\fldigi-[VERSION]`".

To pass parameters, use `--params "''"`
(e.g  `choco install flrig --params="'/DIR:c:"\fldigi" /ITEM2:value2 /FLAG_BOOLEAN'"`).

To have choco remember parameters on upgrade, be sure to set:
`choco feature enable -n=useRememberedArgumentsForUpgrades`
]]></description>
